  "text": "Loss of lumbar lordosis after fusion has been suggested to be a reason for the degeneration of the adjacent segments. [CITATION_1] Umehara et al reported that after L4 -L5 fusion in 18 patients, lordosis in the fusion segment decreased 3°after surgery and increased in the proximal 2 segments by 2°each. [CITATION_2] Long-term clinical results were not reported on these patients, and thus it is unclear if these changes lead to symptomatic adjacent level degeneration. Although the current results describe a 2°de-crease in lordosis from L2 to L5, no deleterious effects were noted in the kinematics at the adjacent levels. The one statistically significant effect at L4 -L5 from neutral to extension was actually a decrease in motion and is likely not clinically significant.",
